---
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Picture } from "astro:assets";
import workyImage from "@assets/images/worky-400x400.png";
import SectionHead from "@components/portfolio/SectionHead.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <main class="page" style="position: relative; min-height: 100vh;">
    <header
      style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; margin-bottom: 32px;"
    >
      <h1 style="font-size: 17px; font-weight: 500; margin: 0;">worky</h1>
      <a href="/" class="home-link" style="font-size: 13px;">← home</a>
    </header>

    <section
      style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 12px;"
    >
      <div
        class="sticky-frame"
        style="--paper-bg: #f1ebe2; padding: 16px; transform: rotate(-0.6deg); display: inline-block;"
      >
        <Picture
          alt="Worky project image"
          src={workyImage}
          formats={["avif"]}
          width={800}
          height={800}
          style="display: block; max-width: 100%; height: auto; width: 320px;"
        />
      </div>
      <p
        class="mono"
        style="font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--ink-2); margin: 8px 0 0;"
      >
        macos desktop organizer
      </p>
    </section>

    <div
      style="margin-top: 24px; display: flex; gap: 18px; flex-wrap: wrap;"
    >
      <a href="/" class="social-link">visit website</a>
      <a
        href="https://www.producthunt.com/p/worky/worky"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="social-link">view on producthunt</a
      >
    </div>

    <section style="margin-top: 64px;">
      <SectionHead label="about" />
      <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--ink); max-width: 520px;">
        Worky is a macOS menu bar tool that keeps your desktop organized and
        clutter-free. It lets you create workspaces (groups of related files)
        and switch between them as needed. And when you want a distraction-free
        environment, Worky clears your desktop and safely stores everything for
        quick access later.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <SectionHead label="nerd notes" />
      <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--ink); max-width: 520px;">
        With worky, keeping the app state sane was a massive pain in the ass,
        that it almost made me give up on this one, but neveeer!!!!. Tracking
        workspaces, serializing/deserializing them reliably, and especially
        dealing with all the chaos when users mess with their folders outside
        the app (or while it's closed) meant hunting down a ton of nasty edge
        cases and building a proper little state machine under the hood. Gotta
        say – I'm pretty damn proud of this bad boy ;) If you get a chance,
        check it out!
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
